<p>Tuesday 16th Oct 1917<br/>I am writing this in Clerke's room while he has his tea. I am on draft, packed up ready to go, paid &amp; expecting the final move in two or three days.<br/>Last night we had our 5th debate &amp; reached the pinnacle of success.<br/>We had had gradually increasing success with the others &amp; the 4th produced an audience of such dimensions that the Quiet room was not large enough to hold it, so this was held in the main room of the Y.M.C.A.<br/>Owing to the usual drawing on &amp; breaking of promises (this time by a clergyman private), I had</p>
